TITLE: Copying Text to Clipboard in GTK 4
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to copy text from a GtkEditable widget to the clipboard using the new GdkClipboard API in GTK 4.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gnome/gtk/blob/main/docs/reference/gtk/migrating-3to4.md#2025-04-18_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
static void
copy_text (GtkWidget *widget)
{
  GtkEditable *editable = GTK_EDITABLE (widget);

  // Initialize a GValue with the contents of the widget
  GValue value = G_VALUE_INIT;
  g_value_init (&value, G_TYPE_STRING);
  g_value_set_string (&value, gtk_editable_get_text (editable));

  // Store the value in the clipboard object
  GdkClipboard *clipboard = gtk_widget_get_clipboard (widget);
  gdk_clipboard_set_value (clipboard, &value);

  g_value_unset (&value);
}
```

