TITLE: Implementing Icon Hashing Function in C
DESCRIPTION: This function calculates a hash value for an icon name string. It's used for the hash table in the icon theme cache format. The hash function should not be implemented by directly calling g_str_hash(), and for optimal results, the number of buckets should typically be prime.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gnome/gtk/blob/main/docs/iconcache.txt#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
unsigned int
icon_str_hash (gconstpointer key)
{
  const char *p = key;
  unsigned int h = *p;

  if (h)
    for (p += 1; *p != '\0'; p++)
      h = (h << 5) - h + *p;

  return h;
}
```

